div.portfolio-modal.modal.fade(id="portfolioModalRRBS" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="portfolioModalRRBSLabel" aria-hidden="true")
  .modal-dialog.modal-xl
    .modal-content
      .modal-header.border-0
        button.btn-close(type="button" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close")
      .modal-body.text-center.pb-5
        .container
          .row.justify-content-center
            .col-lg-8
              // Portfolio Modal - Title
              h2.portfolio-modal-title.text-secondary.text-uppercase.mb-0#portfolioModalRRBSLabel RRBS Analysis
              // Icon Divider
              .divider-custom
                .divider-custom-line
                .divider-custom-icon
                  i.fas.fa-star
                .divider-custom-line
              // Portfolio Modal - Image
              img.img-fluid.rounded.mb-5(src="assets/img/portfolio/EM-Seq.png" alt="...")
              // Portfolio Modal - Text
              p.mb-4 Reduced Representation Bisulfite Sequencing (RRBS) using Illumina short reads is a cost-effective method for analyzing DNA methylation at single-base resolution in CpG-rich regions of the genome. This technique involves digesting DNA with restriction enzymes, treating the DNA with bisulfite to convert unmethylated cytosines to uracil, sequencing the treated DNA, and mapping the sequences to a reference genome.
              p.mb-4 Bioinformatics services I can provide from RRBS data include:
              ul
                li Data preprocessing: Quality control, filtering, and trimming of raw sequencing reads.
                li Read alignment: Mapping bisulfite-treated reads to a reference genome.
                li Methylation calling: Identifying methylated cytosines and quantifying methylation levels.
                li Differential methylation analysis: Comparing methylation patterns between conditions.
                li Functional annotation: Annotating differentially methylated regions with genomic features and performing pathway enrichment analyses.
                li Integration with other omics data: Combining RRBS data with other types of data (e.g., RNA-Seq, ChIP-Seq) for multi-omics analysis.
                li Custom pipeline development: Developing tailored bioinformatics pipelines for specific research questions.
                li Visualization: Creating visual representations of methylation data and results.
              button.btn.btn-primary(data-bs-dismiss="modal")
                i.fas.fa-times.fa-fw
